dcterms:description: The SBM PATTERN set is used for graph pattern recognition tasks, consisting of 10K items in the train set, 2K in the validation set, and 2K in the test set. Each graph has on average 117.47 nodes and 2 classes.
dcterms:title: SBM PATTERN

dcterms:description: The SBM CLUSTER dataset is used for semi-supervised graph clustering tasks, with 10K graphs for training, 1K for validation, and 1K for testing. Each graph has an average of 117.20 nodes and 6 classes.
dcterms:title: SBM CLUSTER

dcterms:creator: Teague Sterling
John J. Irwin
dcterms:description: The ZINC dataset is used for regressing molecular constrained solubility, containing 10K training graphs, 1K validation graphs, and 1K test graphs, with each graph containing an average of 23.16 nodes.
dcterms:title: ZINC

dcterms:description: The TSP dataset is used to evaluate edge classification performance, with 10K training graphs, 1K validation graphs, and 1K test graphs. Each graph has a different number of nodes, with an average of 275.76 nodes.
dcterms:title: TSP

dcterms:description: The miniImageNet dataset is used for few-shot learning tasks, containing 100 classes with 600 images for each class, split into training, validation, and testing sets.
dcterms:title: miniImageNet

dcterms:description: The IMDB-MULTI dataset is a graph classification benchmark where each actor/actress's ego-network forms a graph representing one of three genres. There are 1500 graphs in this dataset.
